 Amiga Channel Issue #11.

 Amiga  Channel  is  an  electronic  magazine  written in Spain for all the
Spanish  and  Latin  Amiga Users.  This magazine contains information about
Amiga  Today,  besides  numerous informative articles, charts, previews and
comments about the best games, programs and also Scene news.
 Amiga  Channel is FreeWare.  This means you have got to pay nothing to get
it.   However,  if  you include it in a CD-Rom or a disk of a magazine, you
must  send  us  a  copy of the CD-Rom or the disk fully free to this postal
address:

   "Amiga Channel"
     Po BOX #720
   pc 29080 Málaga
        SPAIN

Christmas  passed,  and  full  of spirit, the untiring 'Amiga Channel' team
returns  again  with  a new edition, the eleventh one.  And, What an issue!
This  issue  presents numerous contents, tons of news, analysis, tutorials,
interviews, games, humor, etc.

The  star  report  of  this  edition  is the publication of the survey that
'Amiga Channel' has prepared'.  We've asked several important personalities
in  the Amiga World about the best and the worst of the last year, and what
they expect for the future.  Also we've asked them wich future they predict
for the new PowerPC.
Among  the  answers we've received, we must mention the Petro Tischtschenko
(president  of  Amiga  International) ones, 'ClickBoom', 'Vulcan Software',
'ICOA', and more.

 
Besides, in this edition we include several and interesting articles, about
how  to  put music in your web page, or how to install an LCD screen in the
Amiga,  apart  of  a  comparative  between two AVI visualizers:  'Avid' and
'CyberAVI'.   Also  we  introduce you some utilities like the revolutionary
'MagicTV', whose programmer has been interviewed by us.
 
In  the  Games  section,  we  remark  three  games  that appeared recently,
'Championship  Manager  2',  'The Final Odyssey' and 'Myst', in addition to
know  how  the  Top-10  is  going,  and we discover for you tricks for some
games.

In  the  music section we offer you the second part of 'Musical Market' and
an extract of the tutorial about "Bars&Pipes".
 
We  couldn't  forget  our usual meeting with the Priest Newton, who in this
edition  answer  several  ethical  doubts,  apart from explain us the Amiga
Genesis,  what  you  must  do  to be a good Amiga user, and the traditional
preaching of New Year.

We  also  offer you information about the last campaigns in favor of Amiga,
'Project Magic' for 'Opera Software' to carry their navigator to the Amiga,
and 'Organica', a revolutionary shaping software by the 'Imagine' creators.

As  tutorials,  we  introduce  you  a  little  in the exciting world of the
Stereography  with  'Personal  Paint',  we begin an 'AREXX' tutorial and we
comment some tircks to work better with 'CygnusED'.
 
And  if  we  tell you 'Amiga Channel' is free, What are you waiting to read
it?     You'll    be    able    to    find   it   in   the   SAU   Web   at
http://www.arrakis.es/amiga/ or in any Aminet mirror.

All  of  this  and  much  more than this in the only magazine that makes it
possible, 'Amiga Channel'.
 
